Egypt’s  national team captain Mohamed Salah  is boasting  the Pharaohs will edge  the Super Eagles  in their opening Group D   Africa Cup of Nations AFCON)  tie  in Garoua today. Already picked  as one of the standout matches  of the on-going  delayed Cameroon 2021 AFCON , the Liverpool star admitted  the tie would be tricky  in view  of the calibre of players at the disposal  of  both sides .  “All teams have top players and have the opportunity to compete,” the  two-time African Footballer of the Year noted at the pre-match conference. “Tomorrow (today)  will do everything we can to win because we have a good team and great players. “We are in the stage of building a new generation, however, we have reached the play-offs in the World Cup qualifiers, and now we will compete for the Africa Cup of Nations.   BREAKING (AFCON 2021): Super Eagles starting XI against…     Nigeria faces testy tie against Egypt in AFCON     Eguavoen: Eagles’ win greater than personal glory   “ I have never won a title with the national team and I hope this will be the first. We have a great coach and a great team so we will give our all.” - Advertisement - Egypt are being coached at  this tournament by the vastly experienced  Portuguese  coach Carlos Queiroz  who   echoed  similar sentiments as Salah’s.  “We are ready and eagerly waiting for the start of the journey,” the 68-year-old Queiroz who  once  assisted  former Manchester United  coach Sir Alex Fergusson said,  “ Everyone is ready to give their best. We will face a team that has many great players, but we are ready and we will face them with full force.”